						<div class="postbody">I forgot to contrast the version with flicker off, which I think demonstrates something else important:<br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<a href="./download/file.php?id=9646&amp;mode=view"><img src="./download/file.php?id=9646&amp;t=1" alt="lucky_penguin_no_flicker_interlaced.jpg" /></a><br />
			<span class="gensmall">lucky_penguin_no_flicker_interlaced.jpg [ 1015.76 KiB | Viewed 1166 times ]</span>
		

		<br />
	</div><br /><br />Comparing the ice blocks here to the ones with flicker on, you're actually getting some in-between colours already just from the horizontal halftone patterns VS the NTSC + TV signal degradation.<br /><br />Just food for thought. I don't think either version looks <em>bad</em> at all, but the no-flicker version is definitely <em>better</em> on this TV in my opinion, and it's not to do with the perception of flickering (non-existent because it's 480i 30fps) but just the problem of interlacing.</div>

